    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-29T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-29T21:00:00-05:00" n="814"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/763: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-30T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 30, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 30—12:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>471. Department’s instruction No. 536, July 6, 1931, enclosing memorandum dated
                    July 2.<note n="91" xml:id="d814fn91">Memorandum by Mr. Joseph E. Jacobs of the
                        Division of Far Eastern Affairs, <ref target="#pg_886">p. 886</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Would it be expedient or possible, in matters of personal, status, for the
                    American Government, by supplementary legislation and treaty, to place Chinese
                    aliens under jurisdiction of the Federal courts, thereby permitting use of the
                    reciprocal clause which the British have adopted and which appears to me to be
                    more acceptable than the one proposed by Mr. Weigh?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
